üá¨üáß Mercedes is the most powerful woman in the world. A world in ruin, distopic and futuristic, exploited to the last  made of grass, to the social, economic and ecological collapse. One day the Government decide to eliminate Mercedes, so she starts her running to the freedom. Few loyal people and many bags fallow her: all this things are weights, useful but disposable in end. The government want to use Mercedes like a scapegoat for its sins, for, we have to tell that, you can be really powerful but never enough to destroy the world all alone. Mercedes embodies the selfish and evil part of everyone. We try to hide it but in the end this part of us gives the courage to search for redemption, even when it seems too late. 
I have to mention also the lights, shadows and colours of this novel. They are so real, I've been watching them for hours. A real masterpiece.
